text: Dalby Forest is a forest on the southern slopes of the North York Moors National Park in North Yorkshire, England. It is maintained by the UK Forestry Commission.Dalby Forest at the Forestry Commission == Wildlife == Dalby Forest is home to many species of wildlife such as badgers, and roe deer. There are also many species of trees including oak, beech, ash, alder, hazel and Scots pine (Aldus sylvestris). ==References== Category:Forests of England Category:Geography of North Yorkshire
